{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Person",
  "name": "FULL_NAME",
  "alternateName": "NICKNAME_OR_ALIAS",
  "description": "Brief professional bio describing expertise, role, and background",
  "image": "https://www.yourwebsite.com/person-photo.jpg",
  "url": "https://www.yourwebsite.com/author/author-name",
  "jobTitle": "Job Title / Role",
  "worksFor": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "COMPANY_NAME",
    "url": "https://www.company.com"
  },
  "sameAs": [
    "https://twitter.com/username",
    "https://www.linkedin.com/in/username",
    "https://www.facebook.com/username",
    "https://github.com/username",
    "https://medium.com/@username"
  ],
  "knowsAbout": [
    "AI Optimization",
    "Search Engine Optimization",
    "Content Marketing",
    "Digital Strategy"
  ],
  "email": "email@example.com",
  "telephone": "+1-XXX-XXX-XXXX",
  "address": {
    "@type": "PostalAddress",
    "addressLocality": "City Name",
    "addressRegion": "ST",
    "addressCountry": "US"
  },
  "alumniOf": {
    "@type": "EducationalOrganization",
    "name": "University Name"
  },
  "award": [
    "Award or Recognition 1",
    "Award or Recognition 2"
  ],
  "publishingPrinciples": "https://www.yourwebsite.com/editorial-guidelines"
}

<!-- 
INSTRUCTIONS:
1. Replace all placeholder values with actual person information
2. Use high-quality professional photo (400x400 minimum)
3. Include all relevant social media profiles in sameAs
4. List expertise areas in knowsAbout array
5. Only include information that's publicly available
6. Remove optional fields if not applicable

REQUIRED FIELDS:
- @context, @type, name

RECOMMENDED FIELDS:
- image, url, jobTitle, sameAs, knowsAbout

OPTIONAL BUT VALUABLE:
- description, worksFor, email, alumniOf, award, publishingPrinciples

USE CASES:

Author Profile:
Use on author bio pages, bylines, and contributor pages to establish expertise and authority.

Expert/Consultant:
Showcase credentials, specializations, and professional background for E-E-A-T signals.

Team Member:
Display on team/about pages to highlight employee expertise and qualifications.

Speaker/Influencer:
Build authority for thought leaders, speakers, and industry experts.

EXPERTISE AREAS (knowsAbout):

Add 3-10 specific topics the person has expertise in:
"knowsAbout": [
  "Artificial Intelligence",
  "Machine Learning",
  "Natural Language Processing",
  "AI Ethics",
  "Technical Writing"
]

CREDENTIALS & QUALIFICATIONS:

Include professional credentials:
"hasCredential": [
  {
    "@type": "EducationalOccupationalCredential",
    "credentialCategory": "certification",
    "name": "Certified AI Professional"
  }
]

EDUCATIONAL BACKGROUND:

Include multiple degrees:
"alumniOf": [
  {
    "@type": "EducationalOrganization",
    "name": "MIT",
    "sameAs": "https://www.mit.edu"
  },
  {
    "@type": "EducationalOrganization",
    "name": "Stanford University",
    "sameAs": "https://www.stanford.edu"
  }
]

ADDITIONAL PROPERTIES:

Birth date (if relevant):
"birthDate": "YYYY-MM-DD"

Gender (if relevant):
"gender": "Male/Female/Other"

Nationality:
"nationality": {
  "@type": "Country",
  "name": "United States"
}

Languages spoken:
"knowsLanguage": ["English", "Spanish", "French"]

Honorific prefix/suffix:
"honorificPrefix": "Dr.",
"honorificSuffix": "PhD"

Publications:
"creator": [
  {
    "@type": "Book",
    "name": "Book Title",
    "isbn": "978-X-XXXX-XXXX-X"
  }
]

SOCIAL PROFILES (sameAs):

Include all professional social media profiles:
- LinkedIn (professional network)
- Twitter/X (thought leadership)
- GitHub (developers/technical)
- Medium (writers)
- YouTube (video creators)
- Instagram (visual/lifestyle)
- Facebook (personal brand)
- Personal website/blog

EMPLOYMENT HISTORY:

Current position:
"worksFor": {
  "@type": "Organization",
  "name": "Current Employer",
  "url": "https://employer.com"
}

Previous positions:
"alumniOf": [
  {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Previous Employer 1"
  }
]

PUBLISHING PRINCIPLES:

Link to editorial guidelines:
"publishingPrinciples": "https://www.yourwebsite.com/editorial-policy"

This helps establish trust and transparency for content creators.

E-E-A-T BENEFITS:

Person schema is critical for:
- Author attribution in AI responses
- Expert credibility signals
- Knowledge panel eligibility
- Rich snippet author information
- Voice search answers from experts
- Building topical authority

BEST PRACTICES:
- Keep information accurate and up-to-date
- Use consistent naming across platforms
- Link to verified social profiles only
- Showcase genuine expertise and credentials
- Include real, professional photo
- Update when achievements change
- Be transparent about affiliations
- Focus on professional, not personal, details

PRIVACY CONSIDERATIONS:
- Only include publicly available information
- Don't expose personal contact details unnecessarily
- Consider professional vs. personal profile separation
- Respect individual privacy preferences
- Follow GDPR/privacy regulations

AI PLATFORM IMPACT:
Person schema helps AI platforms:
- Attribute content to qualified experts
- Cite authors with relevant credentials
- Build trust through expert identification
- Verify information sources
- Recommend content from authorities

INTEGRATION WITH ARTICLES:

When using in articles, link to Person schema:
"author": {
  "@type": "Person",
  "@id": "https://www.yourwebsite.com/author/john-smith"
}

Then define full Person schema on the author page with matching @id.
-->
